The President of the United States, Joseph R. Biden Jr., has issued a memorandum delegating authority to the Secretary of State under section 614(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. This delegation allows the Secretary of State to determine whether it is necessary for the security interests of the United States to provide up to $215 million from the Economic Support Fund to address the global COVID-19 pandemic. This authority is granted without being bound by any provision of law within the scope of section 614(a)(1) of the FAA. The memorandum also directs the publication of this delegation in the Federal Register.